\t    this.parent = (Tag) adapteeParent;\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t    // Must be SimpleTag - no other types defined.\n\t\t    this.parent = new TagAdapter((SimpleTag) adapteeParent);\n\t\t}\n\t    }\n\t    parentDetermined = true;\n\t}\n\n\treturn this.parent;\n    }\n    \n    /**\n     * Gets the tag that is being adapted to the Tag interface.\n     * This should be an instance of SimpleTag in JSP 2.0, but room\n     * is left for other kinds of tags in future spec versions.\n     *\n     * @return the tag that is being adapted\n     */\n    public JspTag getAdaptee() {\n        return this.simpleTagAdaptee;\n    }\n\n    /**\n     * Must not be called.\n     *\n     * @return always throws UnsupportedOperationException\n     * @throws UnsupportedOperationException Must not be called\n     * @throws JspException never thrown\n     */\n    public int doStartTag() throws JspException {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException( \n            \"Illegal to invoke doStartTag() on TagAdapter wrapper\" );\n    }\n \n    /**\n     * Must not be called.\n     *\n     * @return always throws UnsupportedOperationException\n     * @throws UnsupportedOperationException Must not be called\n     * @throws JspException never thrown\n     */\n    public int doEndTag() throws JspException {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException( \n            \"Illegal to invoke doEndTag() on TagAdapter wrapper\" );\n    }\n\n    /**\n     * Must not be called.\n     *\n     * @throws UnsupportedOperationException Must not be called\n     */\n    public void release() {\n        throw new UnsupportedOperationException( \n            \"Illegal to invoke release() on TagAdapter wrapper\" );\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777829157931}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test methods**\n\nI’m thinking about using AssertJ for testing under Native. It seems that there might not be a run, which could mean I need to consider source level. I wonder if I should expose a protected get or possibly subclass for better access. The tests should focus on SimpleTagSupport and involve calling public methods like set/get parent, doTag, and findAncestor. Notably, the dynamic call site appears at line 183 only in findAncestor. I must ensure no package-private elements are involved.\n\n**Exploring SimpleTagSupport**\n\nI’m working with SimpleTagSupport and creating a new instance of `MatchingSimpleTag`. This involves setting the parent, then calling `findAncestorWithClass()` for the child. It also checks if `MatchingSimpleTag.class` is assignable from `JspTag.class`, which triggers a certain process. I notice that the class literal for `MatchingSimpleTag.class` was generated in our test rather than the target. I’m considering including a TagAdapter branch, but the active call site is not decisive, so it's better to keep one test file and avoid overdoing it. \n\nMaybe I could include a method like `findAncestorWithClassReturnsNearestSimpleTagParent` to test the hierarchy. Then, I’m also reminded to define interfaces like `Marker` and extend `SimpleTagSupport` with `TaggedParent`. It seems like there’s a consideration regarding `klass.isInterface` checks, especially for `JspTag.class`. I’ll also need to inspect if `TagAdapter` wraps `SimpleTag`.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02f88ff6eff421730169f7851b5aec81929729cb517c1def87\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp94Ul-vWqD5pwVJTTGwmmjeQSqqlmGVrDJ4EOEgrB2OvJk0aYWxFKA6O9fxnqdcSeqKQQVR5CeEv8Eup_VfkEadEl2xyInrmF52Yz1Ik0fdZQJIgAIwmmhUR9xBsGA8DP7EQDbM3-suveQfiJzxgDxvYSARSrwDfxwuSqQPMX_BqI-Gl3ZJC_b6YszxTgAaqT4UdQqALz5s-npPxV3RsZYK8XE_I5_qKlXSO0kQKsrDwtyanHtt3ZFyBcZP